.TH "tty_port_register_device" 9 "tty_port_register_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_port_register_device \- register tty device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct device *" tty_port_register_device
.BI "(struct tty_port *port "  ","
.BI "struct tty_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "unsigned index "  ","
.BI "struct device *device "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
tty_port of the device
.IP "driver" 12
tty_driver for this device
.IP "index" 12
index of the tty
.IP "device" 12
parent if exists, otherwise NULL
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
It is the same as tty_register_device except the provided \fIport\fP is linked to
a concrete tty specified by \fIindex\fP. Use this or tty_port_install (or both).
Call tty_port_link_device as a last resort.
